description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Chief Operating Officer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company: Bexley GP Federation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Bexleyheath, Kent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £80,000 – £110,000 Negotiable + Pension&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting to: BHNC Board of Directors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a very exciting opportunity for an exceptional individual to become the COO of a growing GP Federation in Bexley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Federation supports 22 GP Practices in the Borough, The role requires someone who has both a wealth of Primary Care knowledge and credibility with GPs, but who is also commercially astute and able to take this organisation to a sustainable platform and support the Primary Care Networks (PCN) in Bexley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help develop the organisational wide strategy, build consensus whilst making the end product commercially viable clearly working with general practice and local health partners in helping deliver the objectives of the NHS Plan (2018) will be key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The board consists of GPs, and the successful person will be able to navigate the board through political differences in order to achieve the organisational wide strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful person will have NHS experience, either from an external perspective or internal, and be able to demonstrate the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Strategy Skills with Implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build consensus between clinical input and commercial output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop leadership and build a supportive board&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High Energy Leadership with credibility at GP level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to drive all aspects of an organisation in a cohesive manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop and support the project team and demonstrate success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Budget and financial modelling as well as IG experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the dynamics of business and political environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to present and challenge decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to build positive relationships and engage with key stakeholders at a senior level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of PCN&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key priorities for the Federation include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting more sustainable primary care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More care locally for patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More integrated primary and community care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influencing improvements in health outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Our Company:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bexley Health Neighbourhood Care CIC (Bexley GP Federation) was formed in January 2015 to help general practice respond to future challenges and changes in the provision of healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a non-profit making organisation set up to deliver healthcare services with the support of SEL CCG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Federation is already working to support the Primary Care Network in general practice, a successful GP 8-8 OOH, and supporting the Community Education Provider Network and VTS Scheme.  We are co-located with BHL (Bexley Health Ltd) at River House, Bexley Village KENT and have strong links with the LMC, Bexley Council and local providers.  We are also involved in cross borough working with other SEL Boroughs under the auspices of SEL CCG in delivering co-ordinated response to COVID 19, including ‘Hot Hubs’ with joint planning with Greenwich in particular as our closest neighbour.&lt;/p&gt;
